# LINE MINI App Review Readiness Checklist

## Policy Compliance

- [ ] Confirm the service category is allowed under LINE MINI App policy.
  - **Prohibited categories:** religious organizations, adult bars/night clubs, gambling, certain lending/fundraising, cigarettes/e-cigarettes, weapons/poisons, unapproved medicines or clinical trials.
- [ ] Confirm the privacy policy discloses third-party sharing, timing of sharing, and the correct service provider relationship where a partner builds for a client.
- [ ] Confirm the channel description states the real service, not a vague company slogan. LINE explicitly reviews the channel description.
- [ ] Confirm channel icon, name, description, privacy policy URL, and other user-visible fields are accurate and current.

## Functional Readiness

- [ ] Confirm Review and Published endpoints are functionally aligned before submission.
- [ ] If the app includes reservation/order/payment flows, provide review test scenarios, test accounts, test products, or store data in the review materials.
- [ ] If using in-app purchase, complete its separate approval flow first; otherwise verified review cannot proceed.

## Regional Requirements

- [ ] If operating in **Thailand or Taiwan**, confirm certified provider status before budgeting release timing.

## Post-Review Awareness

- [ ] Be aware that changing these fields after verification triggers **re-review**:
  - Channel icon, name, description
  - Privacy policy URL
  - Linked OA
  - Published endpoint URL
  - Scopes
  - `shareTargetPicker` setting
  - Channel consent simplification state
